{"title_page": "WrestleMania 36", "text_new": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use American English|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|2020 WWE pay-per-view and WWE Network event}}\n<!--{{current sport|sport=pro wrestling|event=WrestleMania}}-->\n{{Infobox Wrestling event\n|name       = WrestleMania 36\n|image      = WrestleMania 36 Poster.jpg\n|caption    = Promotional poster featuring [[John Cena]], [[Charlotte Flair]], [[Roman Reigns]], [[Becky Lynch]], and [[Bray Wyatt|\"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt]]\n|tagline    = Too Big for Just One Night!<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/wrestlemania-36|title=WrestleMania 36|work=WWE|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n|promotion  = [[WWE]]\n|brand      = [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]]<br />[[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]]<br />[[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]]\n|date       = March 25\u201326, 2020\n|date_aired = April 4\u20135, 2020<ref name=\"taped\">{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Mike|title=WWE TAPING UPDATES|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/134914/wwe-taping-updates.html?p=1|publisher=PWInsider|date=March 21, 2020|accessdate=March 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|future     = Y\n|attendance = 0<ref group=Note name=Corona>The event will be held without a live audience due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].</ref>\n|venue      = [[WWE Performance Center]]<br>\n|city       = [[Orlando, Florida]]\n|wwenlast   = [[Elimination Chamber (2020)|Elimination Chamber]]\n|wwennext   = [[Money in the Bank (2020)|Money in the Bank]]\n|event      = [[WrestleMania]]\n|lastevent2 = [[WrestleMania 35|35]]\n|nextevent2 = [[WrestleMania 37|37]]\n}}\n'''WrestleMania 36''' is the ongoing 36th annual [[WrestleMania]] [[professional wrestling]] [[pay-per-view]] and [[WWE Network]] [[List of WWE pay-per-view and WWE Network events|event]] produced by [[WWE]] for their [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]], [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]], and [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] [[WWE brand extension|brand divisions]] \u2014 the first to promote the NXT brand. It was taped on March 25 and 26, 2020; Part 1 aired on April 4 and Part 2 will air on April 5.\n\nOriginally scheduled to take place solely on April 5, 2020 at the [[Raymond James Stadium]] in [[Tampa, Florida|Tampa]] and to air live, WrestleMania 36 was relocated due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]. The promotion announced plans to present the event from the [[WWE Performance Center]] in [[Orlando, Florida|Orlando]] (where all other WWE programming has since originated), and other unannounced locations (later revealed to be a [[Cemetery|boneyard]] and the [[Bray Wyatt#The Fiend and Universal Champion (2019\u2013present)|Firefly Fun House]]), each with [[Behind closed doors (sport)|no spectators in attendance]], and for it to be the first WrestleMania to be broadcast across two nights and the second to be filmed from multiple venues (the first being [[WrestleMania 2]]).\n\n<!--Nine matches were contested during Part 1 of the event. In the main event, [[The Undertaker]] defeated [[AJ Styles]] in a [[Buried Alive match|Boneyard match]]. In other prominent matches, [[Braun Strowman]] defeated [[Goldberg]] to win the [[WWE Universal Championship]], [[Becky Lynch]] defeated [[Shayna Baszler]] to retain the [[WWE Raw Women's Championship|Raw Women's Championship]], and [[Kevin Owens]] defeated [[Seth Rollins]] in a [[No Disqualification match]]-->\n== Production ==\n=== Background ===\n[[WrestleMania]] is considered [[WWE]]'s flagship event, having first been held in [[WrestleMania I|1985]]. It is the longest-running professional wrestling event in history and is held annually between mid-March to mid-April.<ref>{{cite web|title=WrestleMania 29 press conference brings WWE to Radio City Music Hall|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/29/wrestlemania-press-conference-radio-city-music-hall-26103938|publisher=WWE|accessdate=March 31, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130407015228/http://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/29/wrestlemania-press-conference-radio-city-music-hall-26103938|archivedate=April 7, 2013|quote=...&nbsp;WWE's flagship event lights up MetLife Stadium&nbsp;... WrestleMania}}</ref> It was the first of WWE's original four pay-per-views, which includes [[Royal Rumble]], [[SummerSlam]], and [[Survivor Series]], dubbed the \"Big Four\".<ref>{{cite book|first1=Ian|last1=Hamilton|title=Wrestling's Sinking Ship: What Happens to an Industry Without Competition|year=2006|publisher=Lulu|page=160|isbn=9781411612105}}</ref> WrestleMania is ranked the sixth most valuable sports brand in the world by [[Forbes]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/59e62ee431358e542c03d5be/6-wrestlemania/|title=Forbes Fab 40 2017|work=Forbes|accessdate=24 October 2017|date=24 October 2017}}</ref> and has been described as the [[Super Bowl]] of [[sports entertainment]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Gelston|first=Dan|title=WrestleMania is Super Bowl of sports entertainment|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/wrestlemania-super-bowl-sports-entertainment|publisher=[[Associated Press]]|accessdate=March 31, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331101111/http://bigstory.ap.org/article/wrestlemania-super-bowl-sports-entertainment|archivedate=March 31, 2014}}</ref> WrestleMania 36 was the third WrestleMania to be held in the city of Orlando, and the fourth to be held in the state of [[Florida]] (after [[WrestleMania XXIV|XXIV]] and [[WrestleMania 33|33]] also in Orlando, and [[WrestleMania XXVIII|XXVIII]] in [[Miami Gardens, Florida|Miami Gardens]]). The event featured wrestlers from the [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] and [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] [[WWE brand extension|brand divisions]], as well as [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]]\u2014although some NXT wrestlers had appeared in WrestleMania's previously annual battle royals, this was the first WrestleMania to promote the brand, following NXT becoming one of WWE's three major brands in September 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.411mania.com/wrestling/triple-h-discusses-nxt-as-a-third-brand-putting-talent-in-a-position-to-succeed-more/|title=Triple H Discusses NXT as a Third Brand, Putting Talent in a Position to Succeed, More|publisher=411MANIA}}</ref> For the first time, WWE announced that it would also offer the pay-per-view as a digital purchase in the United States via [[FITE TV]], and the [[Fox Sports (United States)|Fox Sports]] app (an expansion of Fox's broadcasts of ''[[WWE SmackDown|SmackDown]]''). [[ESPN]], which does not normally air WWE programming, aired encores of previous editions of WrestleMania during the lead-up to the event.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Behind the Scenes of a Bizarre \u2018WrestleMania 36\u2019|url=https://www.si.com/wrestling/2020/04/03/wwe-wrestlemania-36-behind-the-scenes-info|last=Barrasso|first=Justin|website=Sports Illustrated|access-date=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe event was originally to take place at the [[Raymond James Stadium]] in [[Tampa, Florida|Tampa]] solely on April 5, 2020 and was to air live.<ref>{{Cite web|title=WWE and local dignitaries officially announce that WrestleMania 36 will take place in Tampa Bay in 2020|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/article/official-wrestlemania-36-announcement|work=WWE|access-date=March 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbssports.com/wwe/news/wrestlemania-36-location-wwe-returns-to-florida-with-2020-show-in-tampa-bay/|title=WrestleMania 36 location: WWE returns to Florida with 2020 show in Tampa Bay|website=[[CBSSports.com]]|date=March 7, 2019|access-date=May 28, 2019}}</ref> As a result of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], other wrestling promotions began to cancel some of their shows in an attempt to prevent further spreading of the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] virus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/alfredkonuwa/2020/02/29/wwe-and-the-wrestling-world-brace-themselves-for-coronavirus-outbreak/#47e683a6677f|title=WWE And The Wrestling World Brace Themselves For Coronavirus Outbreak|date=February 29, 2020|last=Konuwa|first=Alfred|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=February 29, 2020}}</ref> In speaking with the ''[[Tampa Bay Times]]'' regarding how this outbreak could affect WrestleMania 36, WWE's [[Chief Brand Officer]] [[Stephanie McMahon]] said \"The health and safety of not only our fan base, but also our superstars, really does come first ... We don't want to put anyone in a bad situation ever, regardless of the circumstance. Those are not risks worth taking.\" WWE's Executive Vice President of Special Events John Saboor further noted that they were constantly monitoring global events.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tampabay.com/sports/pro-wrestling/2020/02/27/as-tampas-wrestlemania-date-nears-wwe-watching-coronavirus/|title=As Tampa\u2019s WrestleMania date nears, WWE watching coronavirus|date=February 27, 2020|last=Cridlin|first=Jay|work=Tampa Bay Times|accessdate=February 29, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wtsp.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/how-coronavirus-concerns-are-impacting-tampa-bay-events/67-9d960bed-c5dc-4db0-82be-3c04fda72328|title=How coronavirus concerns are impacting Tampa Bay area events|date=March 10, 2020|last=Burch|first=Liz|work=[[WTSP]]|publisher=[[Tegna Inc.]]|accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref> A meeting was held by Tampa officials on March 12 to determine the fate of WrestleMania 36; it was decided that the event would still proceed as planned, barring that the situation did not worsen in a week's time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tampabay.com/sports/2020/03/12/wrestlemania-36-still-on-for-now-but-stay-tuned/|last1=Knight|first1=Joey|last2=Frago|first2=Charlie|title=WrestleMania 36 still on for now ... but stay tuned|date=March 12, 2020|work=Tampa Bay Times|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref> [[Hillsborough County, Florida|Hillsborough County]] Commissioner [[Les Miller (Florida politician)|Les Miller]] further stated that if the situation was not any better by the following week, they would \"pull the plug\" on WrestleMania 36 if WWE did not do it themselves.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2880867-wrestlemania-36-at-risk-of-being-canceled-by-hillsborough-county-in-florida|title=WrestleMania 36 at Risk of Being Canceled by Hillsborough County in Florida|last=Kasabian|first=Paul|website=Bleacher Report|access-date=March 14, 2020}}</ref> WWE then stated that they had a [[contingency plan]] ready in case the event was canceled.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fox13news.com/news/wwe-putting-contingency-plans-in-place-if-hillsborough-county-cancels-wrestlemania-36|title=WWE putting 'contingency plans' in place if Hillsborough County cancels WrestleMania 36|last=Cascio|first=Josh|date=March 13, 2020|website=[[WTVT|FOX13News.com]]|publisher=[[Fox Television Stations]], LLC|access-date=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 16, WWE announced that the event would be held at the [[WWE Performance Center]] in Orlando with only essential personnel in attendance, as with all other WWE weekly programs during this pandemic.<ref>{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WrestleMania officially moved to the WWE Performance Center|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/03/16/wrestlemania-officially-moved-to-the-wwe-performance-center/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=March 16, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=WWE to hold WrestleMania without fans|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/16/us/wwe-wrestlemania-without-fans-trnd/index.html|last=Jackson|first=Amanda|work=[[CNN]]|date=March 16, 2020|access-date=March 16, 2020}}</ref><ref name=NOFANS>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/article/wrestlemania-36-statement|title=WWE statement regarding WrestleMania 36|work=WWE|date=March 16, 2020|accessdate=March 16, 2020}}</ref> WWE then announced that WrestleMania 36 would be split into a two-night event, on April 4 and 5, marking the first WrestleMania to be done over two nights. It was also confirmed that the event would take place at other, unspecified locations, marking the first WrestleMania since [[WrestleMania 2]] in 1986 (which originated from three different venues on the same night) to be held at multiple locations. Former [[National Football League]] (NFL) player [[Rob Gronkowski]], who had recently signed with WWE, was also announced to serve as the host of the event<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/wwe-splits-audience-less-wrestlemania-36-into-two-nights/|title=WWE Splits Audience-Less WrestleMania 36 Into Two Nights|last=Maglio|first=Tony|date=2020-03-18|website=TheWrap|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/wrestlemania-36/article/wrestlemania-36-two-night-wwe-network-rob-gronkowski-host|title=Unprecedented two-night WrestleMania to be hosted by Rob Gronkowski on WWE Network|work=WWE|date=March 17, 2020|accessdate=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\u2014Gronkowski last appeared for WWE at WrestleMania 33 in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/33/article/rob-gronkowski-mojo-rawley-andre-the-giant-memorial-battle-royal|title=Rob Gronkowski helps Mojo Rawley win the Andre the Giant Memorial Battle Royal|date=April 2, 2017|work=WWE|access-date=April 24, 2017}}</ref> It was then reported by ''[[PWInsider]]'' that WWE were pre-taping several episodes of their weekly programs for future broadcasts, as well as WrestleMania itself, between March 21\u201326 (with the exception of the live broadcast of the March 23 episode of ''Raw''). WrestleMania was taped on March 25 and 26, and it will air on [[Broadcast delay|tape delay]] on April 4 and 5.<ref name=\"taped\"/> In an interview with ''[[TV Guide]]'', WWE's Executive Vice President of Global Talent Strategy & Development and part-time wrestler [[Triple H|Paul \"Triple H\" Levesque]] described the taped nature of the event as \"unique\"; noting that with the different settings, there would be \"some matches and some components and things that will take place this year like we've never done before\" in terms of production elements and settings, citing the announced [[No Holds Barred match|Firefly Fun House match]] and [[Buried Alive match|Boneyard match]] (the latter stated to have been shot at a different location) as examples.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/wwe-triple-h-wrestlemania-coronavirus-impact/|title=WWE's Triple H Explains What It's Like to Film WrestleMania Without the Fans|date=April 2, 2020|website=TVGuide.com|access-date=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe card underwent changes due to injuries and issues that arose related to the ongoing pandemic. Wrestlers such as [[Rey Mysterio]], who was reportedly set to face [[Andrade (wrestler)|Andrade]] for the [[WWE United States Championship|United States Championship]], and [[Dana Brooke]], who was originally announced to take part in the [[SmackDown Women's Championship]] elimination match, were pulled from the event due to [[coronavirus]] concerns.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/alfredkonuwa/2020/03/24/wwes-rey-mysterio-and-dana-brooke-quarantined-amid-coronavirus-pandemic/#92ae5684aa44|title=WWE\u2019s Rey Mysterio And Dana Brooke Quarantined Amid Coronavirus Pandemic|date=March 24, 2020|last=Konuwa|first=Alfred|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref> It was also confirmed that WrestleMania's annual battle royals, the [[Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Battle Royal]] and [[WrestleMania Women's Battle Royal]], would not occur at WrestleMania 36 to limit the number of wrestlers in the ring at the same time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prowrestlingsheet.com/wrestlemania-battle-royal-not-taking-place-coronavirus/#.Xn7gnohKg2w|title=WWE Confirms WrestleMania 36 Will Not Feature Battle Royal Matches|date=March 26, 2020|author=[[Ryan Satin|Satin, Ryan]]|work=[[Pro Wrestling Sheet]]|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref> [[Roman Reigns]], who was at an increased risk for COVID-19 due to being in an [[Immunodeficiency|immunocompromised state]] from his previous struggles with [[leukemia]], requested to be removed from his match against [[Bill Goldberg|Goldberg]] and WWE honored the request;<ref name=\"ROmanOUT\">{{cite web|url=https://www.prowrestlingsheet.com/roman-reigns-out-of-wrestlemania-36-match/#.Xn1qDIhKjIV|title=Roman Reigns Out Of WrestleMania 36 Match|author=[[Ryan Satin|Satin, Ryan]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=March 26, 2020|work=[[Pro Wrestling Sheet]]}}</ref><ref name=\"RomanOut2\" /> [[Braun Strowman]] was selected as Reigns' replacement in the match.<ref name=\"BRLIVE\">{{cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2883370-wwe-wrestlemania-36-rumors-braun-strowman-replacing-roman-reigns-vs-goldberg|title=WWE WrestleMania 36 Rumors: Braun Strowman Replacing Roman Reigns vs. Goldberg|author=Chiari, Mike|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 27, 2020|work=[[Bleacher Report]]}}</ref><ref name=SmackDown04032020>{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/03/4-3-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-of-the-final-push-for-wrestlemania-36-with-john-cena-responding-to-bray-wyatts-challenge-to-a-firefly-funhouse-match-miz-tv-with-the-usos-an/|title=4/3 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell\u2019s review of the final push for WrestleMania 36 with John Cena responding to Bray Wyatt\u2019s challenge to a Firefly Funhouse match, Miz TV with The Usos and New Day|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> Andrade, who was scheduled to team with [[Angel Garza]] to face [[The Street Profits]] (Angelo Dawkins and Montez Ford) for the [[Raw Tag Team Championship]],<ref name=\"Raw03232020\"/> was removed from that match due to an injury and was replaced by NXT's [[Austin Theory]].<ref name=\"POLLOCK\">{{cite web|url=https://www.postwrestling.com/2020/03/27/another-wwe-performer-off-wrestlemania-identity-of-replacement/|title=Another WWE performer off WrestleMania, identity of replacement|author=[[John Pollock|Pollock, John]]|work=POST Wrestling|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 27, 2020}}</ref> Additionally it was reported that [[The Miz]] had contracted an illness and was pulled from the WrestleMania card;<ref name=POLLOCK/> this turned the planned [[tag team]] [[Triple Threat match|Triple Threat]] [[Ladder match]] for the [[SmackDown Tag Team Championship]]<ref name=NGH>{{cite web|title=SmackDown Tag Team Champions The Miz & John Morrison vs. The Usos vs. The New Day (Triple Threat Ladder Match)|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/wrestlemania-36/the-miz-john-morrison-vs-the-usos-vs-the-new-day|work=WWE|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref> into a Ladder match between [[The Usos|Jimmy Uso]], [[Kofi Kingston]], and defending champion [[John Morrison (wrestler)|John Morrison]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.f4wonline.com/wwe-news/new-wrestlemania-36-match-updates-cesaro-asuka-murphy-307516|title=NEW WRESTLEMANIA 36 MATCH, UPDATES ON CESARO, ASUKA & MURPHY|author=Nason, Josh|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 27, 2020|work=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WrestleMania 36 Smackdown Tag Title match officially changed|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/04/wrestlemania-36-smackdown-tag-title-match-officially-changed/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=April 4, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> Triple H confirmed that due to the circumstances, nothing would be held against any of the wrestlers who missed the event. He also stated that all of the talent competing were there in a voluntary capacity. Notably, Triple H was also not scheduled to compete at the event, though this was planned before the pandemic; this marks Triple H's first WrestleMania missed since [[WrestleMania 23]] in 2007.<ref name=\"TripleH-ESPN\">{{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z7r8xAp0HSs|title=Triple H remembers his favorite WrestleMania moment, previews WrestleMania 36 \u2013 SportsCenter|date=March 29, 2020|author=[[ESPN]]|medium=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Storylines ===\nThe event included matches that resulted from scripted storylines, where wrestlers portrayed [[Face (professional wrestling)|heroes]], [[Heel (professional wrestling)|villains]], or [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Tweener|less distinguishable characters]] in scripted events that built tension and culminated in a wrestling match or series of matches. Results were predetermined by WWE's writers on the Raw, SmackDown, and NXT brands,<ref name=\"HSW\">{{cite web|title=How Pro Wrestling Works|url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|last=Grabianowski|first=Ed|work=HowStuffWorks|publisher=[[Discovery Communications]]|accessdate=March 5, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDla2zy5?url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|archivedate=November 18, 2013|date=January 13, 2006}}</ref><ref name=WWEnt>{{cite web|title=Live & Televised Entertainment|url=http://corporate.wwe.com/company/events.jsp|publisher=WWE|accessdate=March 21, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5esskNFVE?url=http://corporate.wwe.com/company/events.jsp|archivedate=February 26, 2009}}</ref> while storylines were produced on WWE's weekly television shows, ''[[Monday Night Raw]]'', ''[[Friday Night SmackDown]]'', and ''[[WWE NXT|NXT]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/wwe-smackdown-live-usa-1201782569/|title=WWE's 'Smackdown' Will Move To Live Broadcast On USA (EXCLUSIVE)|last=Steinberg|first=Brian|date=May 25, 2016|website=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=May 25, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526113045/http://variety.com/2016/tv/news/wwe-smackdown-live-usa-1201782569/|archivedate=May 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== World championship matches ====\n\nFeeling as though nobody deserved an opportunity to challenge him at the [[Royal Rumble (2020)|Royal Rumble]] or WrestleMania, Raw's [[WWE Champion]] [[Brock Lesnar]] decided to enter himself into the men's [[Royal Rumble match]] as entrant number one.<ref name=\"Raw01062020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/01/06/01-06-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-brock-lesnars-return-andrade-vs-rey-mysterio-for-the-u-s-championship-the-viking-raiders-vs-the-street-profits-vs-luke-gallows-and-karl-anderson-in-a/|title=01/06 WWE Raw Results: Powell's review of Brock Lesnar's return, Andrade vs. Rey Mysterio for the U.S. Championship, The Viking Raiders vs. The Street Profits vs. Luke Gallows and Karl Anderson in a Triple Threat for the Raw Tag Titles, first show of 2020|date=January 6, 2020|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=January 7, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Raw01202020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/01/20/01-20-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-andrade-vs-rey-mysterio-in-a-ladder-match-for-the-u-s-championship-rusev-and-liv-morgan-vs-bobby-lashley-and-lana-wwe-champion-brock-lesnar-royal/|title=01/20 WWE Raw Results: Powell's review of Andrade vs. Rey Mysterio in a ladder match for the U.S. Championship, Rusev and Liv Morgan vs. Bobby Lashley and Lana, WWE Champion Brock Lesnar, Royal Rumble developments|date=January 20, 2020|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref> Lesnar dominated the first half of the match until he was eventually eliminated by Raw's [[Drew McIntyre]], who would go on and win the match, thus earning himself a world championship match of his choosing at WrestleMania.<ref name=\"RR2020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WWE Royal Rumble results: Powell's live review of the Royal Rumble matches, \"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt vs. Daniel Bryan in a strap match for the WWE Universal Championship, Becky Lynch vs. Asuka for the Raw Women's Championship|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/01/26/wwe-royal-rumble-results-powells-live-review-of-the-royal-rumble-matches-the-fiend-bray-wyatt-vs-daniel-bryan-in-a-strap-match-for-the-wwe-universal-championship-becky-lynch-vs-asuka-for-th/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=January 26, 2020}}</ref> The next night on ''Raw'', McIntyre announced that he would challenge Lesnar for the WWE Championship at the event.<ref name=\"Raw01272020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=01/27 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s review of Edge\u2019s return, Royal Rumble winners Drew McIntyre and Charlotte Flair, Seth Rollins and Buddy Murphy vs. Samoa Joe and Kevin Owens for the Raw Tag Titles, Liv Morgan vs. Lana |url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/01/27/01-27-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-edges-return-royal-rumble-winners-drew-mcintyre-and-charlotte-flair-seth-rollins-and-buddy-murphy-vs-samoa-joe-and-kevin-owens-for-the-raw-tag-titles-l/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=January 28, 2020}}</ref> At [[Super ShowDown (2020)|Super ShowDown]], Lesnar retained the title against [[Ricochet (wrestler)|Ricochet]], keeping him as the defending champion against McIntyre at WrestleMania.<ref name=\"SuperShowDown2020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WWE Super ShowDown results: Powell\u2019s live review of \"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt vs. Goldberg for the WWE Universal Championship, Brock Lesnar vs. Ricochet for the WWE Championship, Big E and Kofi Kingston vs. The Miz and John Morrison for the Smackdown Tag Titles|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/02/27/wwe-super-showdown-results-powells-live-review-of-the-fiend-bray-wyatt-vs-goldberg-for-the-wwe-universal-championship-brock-lesnar-vs-ricochet-for-the-wwe-championship-big-e-and-kofi-kingst/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=February 27, 2020|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\nAfter winning SmackDown's [[WWE Universal Championship|Universal Championship]] at Super ShowDown,<ref name=\"SuperShowDown2020\"/> [[WWE Hall of Fame]]r Goldberg appeared on the following night's episode of ''SmackDown'' and issued an open challenge by stating his catchphrase, \"Who's next?\" Roman Reigns interrupted and had a stare down with Goldberg before accepting his challenge, which was subsequently scheduled for WrestleMania.<ref name=\"SmackDown02282020\">{{cite web|last=Barnett|first=Jake|title=2/28 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Barnett\u2019s review of John Cena\u2019s return, Goldberg\u2019s first appearance since winning the WWE Universal Championship at WWE Super ShowDown|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/02/28/2-28-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-barnetts-review-of-john-cenas-return-goldbergs-first-appearance-since-winning-the-wwe-universal-championship-at-wwe-super-showdown/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=February 29, 2020}}</ref> Just before the event, however, Reigns, requested to be removed from the match for being at an increased risk for COVID-19, as he was in an immunocompromised state from his previous health issues with leukemia; Reigns himself confirmed the report and stated that WWE honored the request.<ref name=RomanOut2>{{cite web|url=https://www.prowrestlingsheet.com/roman-reigns-comments-confirms-wrestlemania-pulling-out/|title=Roman Reigns Comments On Pulling Out Of WrestleMania 36 (VIDEO)|author=[[Ryan Satin|Satin, Ryan]]|work=Pro Wrestling Sheet|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref><ref name=ROmanOUT/> Triple H also confirmed the report in a March 29 interview on [[ESPN]]'s ''[[SportsCenter]]''.<ref name=\"TripleH-ESPN\"/> Five days later on the April 3 episode of ''SmackDown'', Braun Strowman was announced as Reigns' replacement in the match.<ref name=SmackDown04032020/>\n\n==== Undercard matches ====\n[[John Cena]], who had last appeared during ''[[List of WWE Raw special episodes|Raw Reunion]]'' in July 2019, made his return from hiatus during the February 28, 2020 episode of ''SmackDown'' to address his role at WrestleMania. Seemingly announcing his retirement, Cena declared he would not be appearing at the event, stating that WrestleMania spots should be earned. As Cena gave a farewell salute to the audience from the stage, the lights went out. When they illuminated, [[Bray Wyatt|\"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt]] appeared behind Cena. The Fiend then pointed to the WrestleMania sign, signaling a challenge to Cena, who simply nodded in acceptance. A match between the two was then scheduled for the event, being a rematch from [[WrestleMania XXX]] in 2014.<ref name=\"SmackDown02282020\"/> On the March 27 episode, Wyatt challenged Cena to a [[No Holds Barred match|Firefly Fun House match]],<ref name=\"SmackDown03272020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=3/27 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell\u2019s review of Big E and Kofi Kingston vs. The Usos for a shot at the Smackdown Tag Titles at WrestleMania, Drew Gulak vs. Shinsuke Nakamura, Asuka vs. Alexa Bliss, Bray Wyatt\u2019s Firefly Funhouse|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/03/27/3-27-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-of-big-e-and-kofi-kingston-vs-the-usos-for-shot-at-the-smackdown-tag-titles-at-wrestlemania-drew-gulak-vs-shinsuke-nakamura-asuka-vs-alex/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref> and Cena accepted.<ref name=SmackDown04032020/>\n\nAt Super ShowDown, [[AJ Styles]] was a participant in the [[Tuwaiq Trophy]] [[gauntlet match]]. Final participant Rey Mysterio was ambushed backstage by Styles' [[The O.C. (professional wrestling)|O.C.]] teammates [[Luke Gallows]] and [[Karl Anderson]], prompting Styles to declare himself the winner by forfeit. The referee gave Mysterio until the count of ten, during which, the camera cut backstage, showing that [[Gallows and Anderson]] had been attacked by [[The Undertaker]], making a surprise return. Undertaker then made his entrance, taking Mysterio's place, and performed a [[Chokeslam]] on Styles to win the match and the trophy.<ref name=\"SuperShowDown2020\"/> On the following ''Raw'', a disgruntled Styles mocked Undertaker for still wrestling and issued a warning.<ref name=\"Raw03022020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/03/02/3-2-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-aleister-black-vs-aj-styles-seth-rollins-and-murphy-vs-the-street-profits-for-the-raw-tag-titles-beth-phoenix-provides-an-edge-update-shayna-baszler-vs-k/|title=3/2 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s review of Aleister Black vs. AJ Styles, Seth Rollins and Murphy vs. The Street Profits for the Raw Tag Titles, Beth Phoenix provides an Edge update, Shayna Baszler vs. Kairi Sane, Rey Mysterio and Humberto Carrillo vs. Andrade and Angel Garza|date=March 2, 2020|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=March 3, 2020}}</ref> The Undertaker then appeared at Elimination Chamber and cost Styles his [[No Disqualification match]] with [[Aleister Black]].<ref name=\"EC2020\"/> The following night on ''Raw'', Styles taunted Undertaker by bringing up his wife [[Michelle McCool]], blaming her for why Undertaker keeps coming back to wrestle. Styles then challenged Undertaker to a match at WrestleMania.<ref name=\"Raw03092020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/03/09/3-9-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-edge-returning-following-randy-ortons-attack-on-beth-phoenix-rey-mysterio-vs-angel-garza-drew-mcintyre-in-action-the-build-to-wrestlemania-kicks-in/|title=3/9 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s review of Edge returning following Randy Orton\u2019s attack on Beth Phoenix, Rey Mysterio vs. Angel Garza, Drew McIntyre in action, the build to WrestleMania kicks in|date=March 9, 2020|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref> A contract signing for the match was conducted the following week.<ref name=\"Raw03162020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/03/16/3-16-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-austin-316-day-with-steve-austin-undertaker-vs-aj-styles-contract-signing-for-wrestlemania-first-raw-at-the-fan-free-wwe-performance-center/|title=3/16 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s review of Austin 3:16 Day with Steve Austin, Undertaker vs. AJ Styles contract signing for WrestleMania, first Raw at the fan-free WWE Performance Center|date=March 16, 2020|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=March 16, 2020}}</ref> Styles then challenged Undertaker to a [[Buried Alive match|Boneyard match]],<ref name=\"Raw03232020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/03/23/3-23-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-randy-orton-responding-to-edges-wrestlemania-challenge-brock-lesnars-appearance-the-build-to-wrestlemania-36-continues/|title=3/23 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s review of Randy Orton responding to Edge\u2019s WrestleMania challenge, Brock Lesnar\u2019s appearance, the build to WrestleMania 36 continues|date=March 23, 2020|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref> and Undertaker accepted, cutting a promo akin to his \"American Bad Ass\" gimmick (circa 2000\u20132003).<ref name=\"Raw03302020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/03/30/3-30-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-the-brands-final-push-for-wrestlemania-36-featuring-becky-lynch-undertaker-brock-lesnar-and-edge/|title=3/30 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s review of the brand\u2019s final push for WrestleMania 36 featuring Becky Lynch, Undertaker, Brock Lesnar, and Edge|date=March 30, 2020|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\nAt the Royal Rumble, Raw's [[Charlotte Flair]] won the women's Royal Rumble match to earn herself a women's championship match of her choosing at WrestleMania.<ref name=\"RR2020\"/> On the February 3 episode of ''Raw'', Flair stated that she had defeated the women's champions of both Raw and SmackDown and had held those titles multiple times. She was then interrupted by [[Rhea Ripley]], the [[NXT Women's Champion]]\u2014a title that Flair had only held once during NXT's infancy in 2014. Ripley declared that Flair should challenge her as she had defeated Flair, but Flair had never beat her.<ref name=\"Raw02032020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/02/03/2-3-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-seth-rollins-vs-ricochet-vs-bobby-lashley-in-a-triple-threat-for-a-shot-at-the-wwe-championship-at-wwe-super-showdown-randy-orton-addresses-his-attack-on-ed/|title=2/3 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s review of Seth Rollins vs. Ricochet vs. Bobby Lashley in a Triple Threat for a shot at the WWE Championship at WWE Super ShowDown, Randy Orton addresses his attack on Edge, Liv Morgan vs. Lana rematch|date=February 3, 2020|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=February 4, 2020}}</ref> Flair continued to delay giving an answer until after Ripley had defended her title at [[NXT TakeOver: Portland|TakeOver: Portland]] on February 16.<ref name=\"NXT02052020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/02/05/2-5-nxt-tv-results-moores-review-of-charlotte-flair-responding-to-rhea-ripleys-wrestlemania-challenge-ripley-and-bianca-belair-meeting-face-to-face-going-into-their-title-match-at-nxt-takeover/|title=2/5 NXT TV results: Moore\u2019s review of Charlotte Flair responding to Rhea Ripley\u2019s WrestleMania challenge, Ripley and Bianca Belair meeting face to face going into their title match at NXT Takeover: Portland, new NXT Cruiserweight Champion Jordan Devlin\u2019s appearance|date=February 5, 2020|last=Moore|first=John|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Raw02102020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/02/10/2-10-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-becky-lynch-vs-asuka-for-the-raw-womens-championship-seth-rollins-murphy-and-aop-vs-samoa-joe-kevin-owens-and-the-viking-raiders-in-an-eight-man-tag/|title=2/10 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s review of Becky Lynch vs. Asuka for the Raw Women\u2019s Championship, Seth Rollins, Murphy, and AOP vs. Samoa Joe, Kevin Owens, and The Viking Raiders in an eight-man tag match, the build to WWE Super ShowDown continues|date=February 10, 2020|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=February 10, 2020}}</ref> After Ripley retained her title at the NXT event, she was ambushed by Flair, who accepted Ripley's challenge for a match at WrestleMania, marking the first time that a Royal Rumble winner chose an NXT championship to challenge for with the title itself being the first NXT championship to be defended at the event.<ref name=\"NXTPortland\">{{cite web|last=Moore|first=John|title=2/16 NXT Takeover: Portland results \u2013 Moore\u2019s live review of Adam Cole vs. Tommaso Ciampa for the NXT Championship, Rhea Ripley vs. Bianca Belair for the NXT Women\u2019s Championship, Bobby Fish and Kyle O\u2019Reilly vs. Matt Riddle and Pete Dunne for the NXT Tag Titles, Finn Balor vs. Johnny Gargano|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/02/16/2-16-nxt-takeover-portland-results-moores-live-review-of-adam-cole-vs-tommaso-ciampa-for-the-nxt-championship-rhea-ripley-vs-bianca-belair-for-the-nxt-womens-championship-bobby-fish-and-kyl/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=February 16, 2020|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\nPrior to [[Survivor Series (2019)|Survivor Series]], a rivalry began between Raw's [[Becky Lynch]] and NXT's [[Shayna Baszler]]. At the event, Baszler won the non-title brand supremacy [[Triple Threat match]] between the three brands' women's champions by submitting SmackDown Women's Champion [[Bayley (wrestler)|Bayley]]. An irate Lynch attacked Baszler following the match and put her through an announce table.<ref name=\"SSeries2019\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WWE Survivor Series results: Powell's live review of Brock Lesnar vs. Rey Mysterio in a No Holds Barred match for the WWE Championship, \"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt vs. Daniel Bryan for the WWE Universal Championship, Becky Lynch vs. Shayna Baszler vs. Bayley in a non-title match|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/11/24/wwe-survivor-series-results-powells-live-review-of-brock-lesnar-vs-rey-mysterio-in-a-no-holds-barred-match-for-the-wwe-championship-the-fiend-bray-wyatt-vs-daniel-bryan-for-the-wwe-uni/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=November 24, 2019|accessdate=November 24, 2019}}</ref> After losing the NXT Women's Championship,<ref name=\"NXT12182019\">{{cite web|last=Moore|first=John|title=12/18 NXT TV results: Shayna Baszler vs. Rhea Ripley for the NXT Women\u2019s Championship, Adam Cole vs. Finn Balor for the NXT Championship|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/12/18/12-18-nxt-tv-results-shayna-baszler-vs-rhea-ripley-for-the-nxt-womens-championship-adam-cole-vs-finn-balor-for-the-nxt-championship/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=December 18, 2019|accessdate=December 18, 2019}}</ref> Baszler appeared as the thirtieth entrant in the women's Royal Rumble match, finishing as the runner-up.<ref name=\"RR2020\"/> Following Lynch's title defense on the February 10 episode of ''Raw'', Baszler ambushed Lynch and bit the back of her neck, thus reigniting their feud.<ref name=\"Raw02102020\"/> Baszler was then entered into Raw's women's [[Elimination Chamber]] match at the [[Elimination Chamber (2020)|namesake event]] where she single-handedly eliminated all of her opponents to win and earn herself a [[Raw Women's Championship]] match against Lynch at WrestleMania.<ref name=\"EC2020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WWE Elimination Chamber results: Powell\u2019s live review of Shayna Baszler vs. Asuka vs. Ruby Riott vs. Liv Morgan vs. Sarah Logan vs. Natalya in an Elimination Chamber match for a shot at the Raw Women\u2019s Championship at WrestleMania 36, Smackdown Tag Title Elimination Chamber match|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/03/08/wwe-elimination-chamber-results-powells-live-review-of-shayna-baszler-vs-asuka-vs-ruby-riott-vs-liv-morgan-vs-sarah-logan-vs-natalya-in-an-elimination-chamber-match-for-a-shot-at-the-raw-women/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=March 8, 2020|accessdate=March 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\nAfter being forced to retire in 2011 due to a severe neck injury, WWE Hall of Famer [[Edge (wrestler)|Edge]] returned at the 2020 Royal Rumble during the namesake match, where he had a brief reunion with [[Randy Orton]]; Edge eliminated Orton before his own elimination.<ref name=\"RR2020\"/> On the following ''Raw'', Edge explained how he was able to make his return. Orton then welcomed Edge back and suggested reforming [[Rated-RKO]], but turned on Edge and performed an RKO on him. After attacking Edge's neck with a chair, Orton smashed Edge's head between two chairs in a maneuver known as the \"Conchairto\", which Edge had made famous.<ref name=\"Raw01272020\"/><ref name=\"Raw02102020\"/><ref name=\"Raw02172020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=2/17 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s review of Randy Orton vs. Matt Hardy in a No Holds Barred match, Aleister Black vs. Erick Rowan, Humberto Carrillo and Rusev vs. Angel Garza and Bobby Lashley, Seth Rollins delivers a sermon|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/02/17/2-17-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-randy-orton-vs-matt-hardy-in-a-no-holds-barred-match-aleister-black-vs-erick-rowan-humberto-carrillo-and-rusev-vs-angel-garza-and-bobby-lashley-seth-rol/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=February 17, 2020|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref> Edge's wife and fellow Hall of Famer [[Beth Phoenix]] appeared on the March 2 episode to give a medical update on her husband. Orton interrupted and said that he attacked Edge so that he would remain at home and continue being a husband and a father to their children. He then blamed Phoenix for the attack, claiming that she allowed Edge to get back in the ring. Phoenix slapped Orton, who in turn performed an RKO on her.<ref name=\"Raw03022020\"/> Edge made his return the following week on [[Montel Vontavious Porter]]'s (MVP) talk show, the \"VIP Lounge\". Orton attempted to attack Edge, only for Edge to perform an RKO of his own on Orton. After Orton retreated, Edge performed the Conchairto on MVP as a warning to Orton.<ref name=\"Raw03092020\"/> Edge then challenged Orton to a [[Last Man Standing match]] at WrestleMania,<ref name=\"Raw03162020\"/> and Orton accepted.<ref name=\"Raw03232020\"/>\n\nAt Survivor Series, [[Seth Rollins]] served as the captain of Team Raw for the men's [[Survivor Series elimination match]], but questioned [[Kevin Owens]]' loyalty to the team due to Owens appearing at [[NXT TakeOver: WarGames (2019)|NXT TakeOver: WarGames]]; Raw suffered a devastating loss at Survivor Series, only winning one of the seven interbrand matches.<ref name=\"SSeries2019\"/> Rollins criticized the Raw roster for their poor performance and again questioned Owens' loyalty, who responded by performing a Stunner on Rollins. Owens then became the target of [[The Authors of Pain|AOP]] ([[Akam (wrestler)|Akam]] and [[Rezar (wrestler)|Rezar]]).<ref name=\"Raw11252019\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/11/25/11-25-wwe-raw-results-powells-review-of-the-night-after-survivor-series-edition-with-aj-styles-vs-humberto-carrillo-for-the-u-s-championship-charlotte-flair-vs-asuka-seth-rollins-town-hall-m/|title=11/25 WWE Raw Results: Powell's review of the night after Survivor Series edition with AJ Styles vs. a four-way winner for the U.S. Championship, Charlotte Flair vs. Asuka, Seth Rollins' town hall meeting|date=November 25, 2019|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=November 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://slam.canoe.com/Slam/Wrestling/2019/11/25/22803055.html|title=RAW: Seth Rollins calls out the RAW roster after a poor Survivor Series|website=canoe.com|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref> Although Owens accused Rollins of being behind AOP's attacks, Rollins denied the accusations, though he ultimately joined with AOP, turning heel. Rollins then began to refer to himself as the \"Monday Night Messiah\" and recruited [[Buddy Murphy|Murphy]] into his new faction with AOP; Rollins and Murphy eventually won the Raw Tag Team Championship together. At the Royal Rumble, Rollins eliminated Owens from the namesake match thanks to help from AOP and Murphy.<ref name=\"RR2020\"/> Rollins and Murphy lost their titles on an episode of ''Raw'', and during a rematch at Elimination Chamber, Owens cost them their match and performed a Stunner on Rollins afterward.<ref name=\"EC2020\"/> The following night on ''Raw'', Rollins challenged Owens to a match,<ref name=\"Raw03092020\"/> and Owens accepted for WrestleMania.<ref name=\"Raw03162020\"/>\n\nOn the Survivor Series Kickoff pre-show, Heavy Machinery ([[Otis Dozovic|Otis]] and [[Tucker Knight|Tucker]]) participated in an interbrand tag team battle royal that was won by [[Dolph Ziggler]] and [[Robert Roode]];<ref name=\"preSSeries2019\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WWE Survivor Series Kickoff Show results: Powell's live review of Lio Rush vs. Kalisto vs. Akira Tozawa for the NXT Cruiserweight Championship|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/11/24/wwe-survivor-series-kickoff-show-results-powells-live-review-of-lio-rush-vs-kalisto-vs-akira-tozawa-for-the-nxt-cruiserweight-championship/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=November 24, 2019|accessdate=November 24, 2019}}</ref> the two teams entered into a feud following the event. Also during this time, Otis started a romance with [[Mandy Rose]]. On the February 14 episode of ''SmackDown'', Otis had a scheduled [[Valentine's Day]] date with Rose; however, Ziggler arrived first and stole the date, causing Otis to walk away heartbroken.<ref name=\"SmackDown02142020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=2/14 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell's review of Roman Reigns and a mystery partner vs. The Miz and John Morrison, Bayley vs. Carmella for the Smackdown Women's Championship, Otis and Mandy Rose's Valentine's Day date|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/02/14/2-14-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-of-roman-reigns-and-a-mystery-partner-vs-the-miz-and-john-morrison-bayley-vs-carmella-for-the-smackdown-womens-championship-ot/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=February 14, 2020|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}</ref> On the March 6 episode, Otis apologized to Rose, who rejected the apology.<ref name=\"SmackDown03062020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=3/6 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell\u2019s review of a tag team gauntlet match, the NWO on A Moment of Bliss, Bray Wyatt\u2019s Firefly Funhouse, Bayley and Sasha Banks vs. Lacey Evans and Naomi, final hype for WWE Elimination Chamber|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/03/06/3-6-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-of-a-tag-team-gauntlet-match-the-nwo-on-a-moment-of-bliss-bray-wyatts-firefly-funhouse-bayley-and-sasha-banks-vs-lacey-evans-and-naomi-f/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 7, 2020}}</ref> Heavy Machinery then participated in the [[SmackDown Tag Team Championship]] Elimination Chamber match, where they were eliminated by Ziggler and Roode.<ref name=\"EC2020\"/> On the March 20 episode of ''SmackDown'', Ziggler distracted Otis during his tag team match by showing pictures of him and Rose together, enraging Otis, which caused Heavy Machinery to get disqualified, thus costing them another title opportunity.<ref name=\"SmackDown03202020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/03/20/3-20-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-of-rob-gronkowskis-appearance-goldberg-and-roman-reigns-contract-signing-for-wrestlemania-36-the-miz-and-john-morrison-vs-heavy-machinery/|title=3/20 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell\u2019s review of Rob Gronkowski\u2019s appearance, Goldberg and Roman Reigns contract signing for WrestleMania 36, The Miz and John Morrison vs. Heavy Machinery in a non-title match|date=March 20, 2020|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref> Ziggler then challenged Otis to a match at WrestleMania and Otis accepted.<ref name=\"SmackDown03272020\"/> On the final ''SmackDown'' before WrestleMania, a mysterious hacker appeared on the  TitanTron during Ziggler's match with Tucker and revealed that Rose's tag team partner [[Sonya Deville]] had conspired with Ziggler to sabotage Rose's date with Otis.<ref name=SmackDown04032020/>\n\n==Event==\n===Night 1===\n{|class=wikitable style=\"font-size:90%; margin: 0.5em 0 0.5em 1em; float: right; clear: right;\"\n|+ '''Other on-screen personnel'''\n!|Role:\n!|Name:\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Hosts\n|[[Rob Gronkowski]]\n|-\n|[[Mojo Rawley]]\n|-\n|rowspan=4|English Commentators\n|[[Michael Cole (wrestling)|Michael Cole]] {{small|(SmackDown)}}\n|-\n|[[John Layfield|John \"Bradshaw\" Layfield]] {{small|(SmackDown)}}\n|-\n|[[Tom Phillips (wrestling)|Tom Phillips]] {{small|(Raw)}}\n|-\n|[[Byron Saxton]] {{small|(Raw)}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Spanish commentators\n|[[Carlos Cabrera]]\n|-\n|[[Marcelo Rodr\u00edguez]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Ring announcer]]s\n|Greg Hamilton {{small|(SmackDown)}}\n|-\n|[[Mike Rome]] {{small|(Raw)}}\n|-\n|rowspan=7|[[Referee (professional wrestling)|Referees]]\n|Danilo Anfibio\n|-\n|[[Kennadi Brink|Jessika Carr]]\n|-\n|[[John Cone]]\n|-\n|Eddie Orengo\n|-\n|[[Charles Robinson (referee)|Charles Robinson]]\n|-\n|[[Drake Younger|Drake Wuertz]]\n|-\n|[[Rod Zapata]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Interviewers\n|Charly Caruso\n|-\n|Kayla Braxton\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Pre-show panel\n|[[Corey Graves]]\n|-\n|[[Peter Rosenberg]]\n|-\n|rowspan=3|Pre-show correspondents\n|[[Renee Young]]\n|-\n|[[Booker T (wrestler)|Booker T]]\n|-\n|[[Mark Henry]]\n|}\n\n====Pre-show====\n\n====Preliminary matches====\n\n====Main event====\n<!--\n===Part 2===\n====Pre-show====\n\n====Preliminary matches====\n\n====Main event====-->\n\n== Results ==\n\n=== Night 1 ===\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|times  = <ref name=\"preWM36Night1\">{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Jason|title=WrestleMania 36 Kickoff Show results: Powell\