{"title_page": "Summertime (DJ Jazzy Jeff & The Fresh Prince song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Summertime\n| cover      = Summertime single.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[DJ Jazzy Jeff & The Fresh Prince]]\n| album      = [[Homebase (album)|Homebase]]\n| released   = May 20, 1991\n| format     = [[CD single|CD]]\n| recorded   = 1990\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]], [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n| length     = 4:30\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Jive Records|Jive]]|[[RCA Records|RCA]]}}\n| writer     = [[Robert Bell (musician)|Robert Bell]], [[Ronald Bell (musician)|Ronald Bell]], [[Kool & the Gang|George \"Funky\" Brown]], [[Kool & the Gang|Robert \"Spike\" Mickens]], [[Outhere Brothers|Lamar Hula Mahone]], Craig Simpkins, [[DJ Jazzy Jeff|Jeffrey A. Townes]], [[Will Smith]](G Syier Hawkins Brown) [[Kool & the Gang|Charles Smith]], [[Kool & the Gang|Alton Taylor]], [[Kool & the Gang|Dennis \"D.T.\" Thomas]], [[Kool & the Gang|Richard Westfield]]\n| producer   = K. Fingers (Craig Simpkins), [[Outhere Brothers|Hula]] (Lamar Hula Mahone), Roland Edison\n| prev_title = [[Yo Home To Bel Air]]\n| prev_year  = 1991\n| next_title = [[Ring My Bell (DJ Jazzy Jeff & The Fresh Prince song)|Ring My Bell]]\n| next_year  = 1991\n}}\n\n\"'''Summertime'''\" is a song by American hip-hop duo [[DJ Jazzy Jeff & The Fresh Prince]]. It was released in May 1991 as the lead single from their fourth studio album, ''[[Homebase (album)|Homebase]]''. The song was produced by Chicago-based producers [[Outhere Brothers|Hula]] & K. Fingers and won a [[Grammy Award]] for [[Best Rap Performance by a Duo or Group]] at the [[1992 Grammy Awards]]. It spent a week at number #1 on the US [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] Chart,<ref>{{cite book |title= Top R&B/Hip-Hop Singles: 1942-2004|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=161}}</ref> as well as reaching #4 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. It also became the duo's first single to enter the top ten of the [[UK Singles Chart]], peaking at #8. The song is written in [[G minor]]. <ref>{{cite book |title= Hot Dance/Disco: 1974-2003|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=79}}</ref>\n\n==Content and reception==\nThe song's instrumention samples \"[[Summer Madness (instrumental)|Summer Madness]]\" by [[Kool & the Gang]].\n\n''[[Rolling Stone]]'' magazine placed it at number 9 in its 2013 \"Best Summer Songs of All Time\", saying: \"Over a funky laidback beat, a young [[Will Smith]] does a fantastic [[Rakim]] impression over a sample of Kool & the Gang's \"Summer Madness\" and drops a sweet ode to hanging out and driving around his native Philly: \"Honking at the honey in front of you with the light eyes/She turn around to see what you beeping at/It's like the summer's a natural aphrodisiac.\" It's still hip-hop's finest summer celebration.\"<ref>[https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-summer-songs-of-all-time-43407/summertime-dj-jazzy-jeff-the-fresh-prince-82680/]</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n; CD Single\n# \"Summertime\" (Single Edit) \u2013 3:57\n# \"Summertime\" (DJ Jazzy Jeff Mix) \u2013 5:37\n# \"Summertime\" (Street Club Remix) \u2013 6:06\n# \"Girls Ain't Nothing But Trouble\" (Shorter Single Edit) \u2013 3:58\n\n; 12\" Vinyl\n# \"Summertime\" (DJ Jazzy Jeff Mix) \u2013 5:37\n# \"Summertime\" (LP Version) \u2013 4:30\n# \"Summertime\" (Instrumental) \u2013 4:30\n# \"Girls Ain't Nothing But Trouble\" (Shorter Single Edit) \u2013 3:58\n\n{{listen\n|filename=Summertime sample.ogg\n|title=\"Summertime\"\n|description=[[DJ Jazzy Jeff & The Fresh Prince]]'s \"Summertime\" from ''[[Homebase (album)|Homebase]]''\n|filetype=[[Ogg]]}}\n\n; American CD Single\n# \"Summertime\" (Single Edit) \u2013 3:57\n# \"Summertime\" (LP Version) \u2013 4:30\n# \"Summertime\" (DJ Jazzy Jeff Mix) \u2013 5:37\n# \"Summertime\" 